```
4.  Non-Solicitation; Non-Disparagement.

    (a) During the Term and for a period of two (2) years after the termination or expiration of this Agreement, neither party shall directly or indirectly through another Person, without the prior written consent of the other party: (i) solicit, induce, encourage, or attempt to solicit, induce or encourage any of the other party's employees to terminate their employment relationship with such other party; or (ii) hire, retain, or engage any of the other party's employees or former employees, if such former employees' employment relationship with the terminating party terminated or expired within one (1) year prior to the date of such hiring, retaining, or engagement; provided, however, that the foregoing restriction shall not apply to a party hiring, retaining, or engaging Persons who respond to a general solicitation for employment or engagement that is not specifically targeted at the other party's employees.

   (b) Each party agrees not to make, or cause or encourage any other Person to make, any disparaging or defamatory comments, orally or in writing, concerning the other party. This Section 4(b) will survive termination of this Agreement
```

```
13. Remedies.
...

(b)Injunctive Relief. The parties acknowledge and agree that, in the judgement of the parties, the restrictions contained in Sections 2, 3, and 4 are reasonable in all respects, and that breach of such Sections by one party would cause immediate, material, and irreparable harm to the other party, which cannot be adequately compenstated with monetary damages. Accordingly, the parties agree that, in the event of a breach or threatened breach by one of the parites of any of the prodvisions of Sections 2,3, or 4, the non-breaching party, with additional rights and remedies existing in its favor at law or in equity, shall be entitled, without the requirement of posting a bond or security, to immediate injuctive and other equitable relief and remedies from any court of competent jurisdiction restoring it to enjoyment of the befits on Section 2, 3, or 4 and enjoining the breaching party from any activity in derogation of such Section, along with reasonable attorney fees and costs in support thererof.
```
